1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with keypoint detection in multiview image streams using neural networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a semi-supervised learning framework using unlabeled data. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of visual tracking, which is relevant to robotics applications. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new end-to-end neural network design. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with processing and analyzing multiview image streams.
